name: Inferno Maw Chiller Beast
text: In the village square, the Inferno Maw awakens, growling with fiery famine. Villagers flee as it consumes apples ablaze, icicles melting in its scorching breath. The blacksmith, eyes wide, whispers of a legend—a beast feasting on flames and fears, the guardian of eternal winter, ever burning, ever hungry.

data.revised_prompt: Imagine a medieval marketplace pulsating with vibrancy and life. At its center looms a large, anthropomorphic refrigerator. This metallic giant is not dormant, instead wreathed in flickering flames lending it a fearsome aura. Its door is transformed into a monstrous mouth, filled with menacing, sharp teeth. From this mouth, a blazing, fiery glow spills out, commanding the attention of the marketgoers as an ominous symbol of its hunger. Outlying this bizarre spectacle, there are multicolored market stalls, attended by vendors and customers alike. Each of them wears an expression that oscillates between awe and fear. Above them, the sky twists with plumes of smoke and fire, mirroring the fridge's fiery display. The cobblestone ground beneath is sprinkled with the charred remains of fruits and vegetables, a grim testament to the fridge's insatiable appetite. The overall image weaves a compelling tapestry of magic, light, and shadow, underlining the fiery and hungry attributes of this fantastical refrigerator.
